    <text type="letter">  
        <body>  
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="duk.00460.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Studio</name>
                    <date when="1891-06-02">June 2 91</date> 
                </dateline>
                <salute>Our beloved brother Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> Han<ptr target="n0285"/> has not be as well&#8212;Hears that you are not so well. grieves that she
                cannot write to you with her own hands&#8212;appreciates you intensely&#8212;</p>            
            <p> And yet Walt she can come down stairs, get her own breakfast&#8212;and care for 
                her own room. her method and spirit remains&#8212;perservering&#8212;.</p>            
            <p> I assist&#8212;do washing&#8212;ever have&#8212;raise water from the 
                well&#8212;purchase all she requires or calls for.</p>            
            <p> I have written to Geo<ptr target="n0700"/> and Lou<ptr target="duk.00615_n6"/>&#8212;but 
                without avail&#8212;</p>           
            <p> Lou could make her a visit, without spending as much money, as she does on tea 
                parties&#8212;as she has written&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Charlie</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
